e souls are always light because more of them have been put out.\n\n- Markus Zusak, The Book Thief\n|\nAlways blow your own trumpet, blowing someone else’s is unhygienic\n\n- Benny\n|\nPrudence is precaution, prudence is protection.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nIf we don’t honor our truth, how can we expect anyone else to do so?\n\n- Alexandra Katehakis, Mirror of Intimacy: Daily Reflections on Emotional and Erotic Intelligence\n|\nTo reach your destination, follow the directions of your heart. It knows the way.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI believe that what we become depends on what our fathers teach us at odd moments, when they aren't trying to teach us. We are formed by little scraps of wisdom.\n\n- Umberto Eco, Foucault's Pendulum\n|\nOut here on the water, it’s a fine line between feeling in control and losing it altogether.\n\n- Laurie Nadel, Dancing with the Wind: A True Story of Zen in the Art of Windsurfing\n|\nOf all the idiots I have met in my life, and the Lord knows they have not been few or little, I think that I have been the biggest.\n\n- Karen\n|\nYour country can be a footstool for God, if he finds people in all spheres of life who will prepare their bodies for the Great King\n\n- Sunday\n|\nThink about the people you love, appreciate, and admire… If today was the last day you could speak with them… What would you say… and what are you waiting for?\n\n- Steve\n|\nThe art is not, to tell. The art is, not to tell.\n\n- Muhammad\n|\nIf you only read books, how will you read the scripture inside you?\n\n- Tapan Ghosh, Faceless The Only Way Out\n|\nThe truth is that you are innately good, wise, and powerful. You were created in and for good.\n\n- Deborah\n|\nNo matter what the cause, God is only as willing as you are.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Unapologetically You: Reflections on Life and the Human Experience\n|\nHe who fears he shall suffer, already suffers what he fears.\n\n- Michel de Montaigne, The Complete Essays\n|\nBe you, be true to your word, don'